quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  7,189,"He is the One Who created you from a single soul, then from it made its spouse so he may find comfort in her. After he had been united with her, she carried a light burden that developed gradually. When it grew heavy, they prayed to God, their Lord, ‚ÄúIf you grant us good offspring, we will certainly be grateful.‚ÄĚ"
  7,190,"But when He granted their descendants good offspring, they associated false gods in what He has given them. Exalted is God above what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ"
  7,191,"Do they associate ňĻwith Godňļ those ňĻidolsňļ which cannot create anything, but are in fact created"
  7,192,"which cannot help them, or even help themselves"
  7,193,"And if you ňĻidolatersňļ call upon them for guidance, they cannot respond to you. It is all the same whether you call them or remain silent"
  7,194,"Those ňĻidolsňļ you invoke besides God are created beings like yourselves. So call upon them and see if they will answer you, if your claims are true"
  7,195,"Do they have feet to walk with? Or hands to hold with? Or eyes to see with? Or ears to hear with? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúCall upon your associate-gods and conspire against me without delay"
  7,196,"‚ÄúIndeed, my Protector is God Who has revealed this Book. For He ňĻaloneňļ protects the righteous"
  7,197,But those ňĻfalse godsňļ you call besides Him can neither help you nor even themselves.‚ÄĚ
  7,198,"If you ňĻidolatersňļ call them to guidance, they cannot hear. And you ňĻO Prophetňļ may see them facing towards you, but they cannot see"
  7,199,"Be gracious, enjoin what is right, and turn away from those who act ignorantly"
  7,200,"If you are tempted by Satan, then seek refuge with God. Surely He is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  7,201,"Indeed, when Satan whispers to those mindful ňĻof Godňļ, they remember ňĻtheir Lordňļ then they start to see ňĻthingsňļ clearly"
  7,202,"But the devils persistently plunge their ňĻhumanňļ associates¬†deeper into wickedness, sparing no effort"
  7,203,"If you ňĻO Prophetňļ do not bring them a sign ňĻwhich they demandedňļ, they ask, ‚ÄúWhy do you not make it yourself?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúI only follow what is revealed to me from my Lord. This ňĻQuranňļ is an insight from your Lord‚ÄĒa guide and a mercy for those who believe.‚ÄĚ"
  7,204,"When the Quran is recited, listen to it attentively and be silent, so you may be shown mercy"
  7,205,"Remember your Lord inwardly with humility and reverence and in a moderate tone of voice, both morning and evening. And do not be one of the heedless"
  7,206,Surely those ňĻangelsňļ nearest to your Lord are not too proud to worship Him. They glorify Him. And to Him they prostrate